Title: BPS States, Weight Spaces and Vanishing Cycles

Comments: for Proceedings of ``Strings 95'', 12p, plain TeX, 6 uuencoded ps

figuresJournal-ref: Nucl.Phys.Proc.Suppl. 46 (1996) 122-129

We review some simple group theoretical properties of BPS states, in relationwith the singular homology of level surfaces. Primary focus is on classical andquantum N=2 supersymmetric Yang-Mills theory, though the considerations can beapplied to string theory as well.